### JWT Roles Debug Tests

@host = https://localhost:7038
@baseUrl = {{host}}/api

### 1. Admin Login (should get Admin and User roles)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "Admin045@gmail.com",
    "password": "admin123"
}

### 2. Regular User Login (should get only User role)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "test@example.com",
    "password": "test123"
}

### 3. Decode Admin Token (replace with actual token from step 1)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/debug/decode-token
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "token": "YOUR_ADMIN_TOKEN_HERE"
}

### 4. Decode User Token (replace with actual token from step 2)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/debug/decode-token
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "token": "YOUR_USER_TOKEN_HERE"
}

### 5. Get Current User Info with Admin Token
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ADMIN_TOKEN_HERE

### 6. Get Current User Info with User Token
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_USER_TOKEN_HERE

### 7. Test Admin Endpoint with Admin Token (should work)
POST {{baseUrl}}/about
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ADMIN_TOKEN_HERE
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "title": "Admin Test",
    "description": "Testing admin access with roles"
}

### 8. Test Admin Endpoint with User Token (should fail)
POST {{baseUrl}}/about
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_USER_TOKEN_HERE
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "title": "User Test",
    "description": "This should fail"
}

### 9. Debug Auth Without Token
GET {{baseUrl}}/about/debug/auth

### 10. Debug Auth With Admin Token
GET {{baseUrl}}/about/debug/auth
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ADMIN_TOKEN_HERE

### 11. Debug Auth With User Token
GET {{baseUrl}}/about/debug/auth
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_USER_TOKEN_HERE